channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump Tells 100K Supporters on Wildwood Beach: ‘We Will Win New Jersey’
North Dakota gov, former presidential candidate Doug Burgum front and center at Trump New Jersey rally
item.description: North Dakota Gov. and former presidential candidate Doug Burgum appeared at Donald Trump’s massive campaign rally in New Jersey on Saturday, fueling speculation he could be Trump's VP pick.

item.title: Trump on 'Antisemites' Funding Biden, Dems: 'Return the Money, Joe'
item.description: Saying he supports "Israel's right to win its war on terror," presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump demanded President Joe Biden and Democrats return the funding from billionaires backing pro-Palestinian and antisemitic protests in the U.S.

item.title: WATCH: 'Queers for Palestine' Block Entrance to Disney World, Then Florida Men Show Up
Trump holds massive beachfront campaign rally for raucous New Jersey crowd: ‘We’re going to win’
item.description: Former President Trump held a rally Saturday in New Jersey, where he predicted he would easily win the Garden State on Election Day in November.

item.title: Trump: I'm 'Going to Be Indicted Into the White House'
item.description: Mocking what he calls President Joe Biden's weaponization of justice against his political opponent, presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump trolled his rival for "indicting him into the White House."

item.title: Newsom's Revised Budget Is a Joke; He's Laughing All the Way to Rome to Pontificate on Climate Change
Border Patrol mobile app for migrants seeking entry into US controversial on both sides of immigration debate
item.description: The Biden administration's use of the CBP One app for asylum seekers, which it says has made the process more efficient, has become controversial for both immigrant and border security advocates.

item.title: Sen. Ricketts to Newsmax: Biden, Israel Relationship Not 'Ironclad'
item.description: The United States has traditionally supported Israel, but President Joe Biden's "ironclad relationship isn't so ironclad," now that he's siding with the "unhinged nut jobs" in the United Nations, Sen. Pete Ricketts told Newsmax Saturday.

item.title: Trump Rally Draws Between 80-100k on the Beach in Wildwood, NJ; May Be 'Largest' in 'State History'
Trump says son Barron, 18, likes politics and gives him advice: ‘He’s a smart one’
item.description: Former President Trump revealed on Friday that his 18-year-old son, Barron, likes politics and sometimes tries to give him policy advice.

item.title: Trump in Long Blue New Jersey: 'We're Expanding the Electoral Map'
item.description: Boldly stepping into the deep blue state of New Jersey, presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump delivered a message to the conservatives at the famed Boardwalk on Saturday night, declaring the state in play this November.

item.title: Schadenfreude, Thy Name Is Clinton: Hillary-Produced Play 'Suffs' Bombs on Broadway
Trump supporters flock to massive New Jersey campaign rally to hear former president speak amid ongoing trials
item.description: Supporters of Donald Trump who went to hear the former president speak at a campaign rally in Wildwood, New Jersey, shared with Fox News Digital why they are supporting him in November.

item.title: Holocaust Survivor to Newsmax: Biden's Ammo Threats Embolden Hamas
item.description: The Biden administration, by threatening to refuse ammunition to Israel for the assault on Rafah, is emboldening Hamas while hindering the Israel Defense Forces' push to eliminate the terror organization that attacked it on Oct. 7, Holocaust survivor Sami Steigmann said.
